		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			SPOILER<BR>
-------<BR>
<BR>
Since I don't do this anymore, I'll give the newbies a spoiler. As you may know, these are lore items for a quest in Kaladim; you may not know that most of the shops in Kelethin are always BURSTING with these belts; if they don't show up in the store's stock, wait until no other characters and too close and buy an item the merchants only have one of, stop talking to the merchant, and then talk to him again and it will likely be in the inventory now. Buy as many as you can afford/carry and bring them to the guy in the basement of Kaladim's Warriors Guild (check quest details for name) and you'll get 1-10 silver, a pw item you can sell for 1-3 gold, plus a whack of exp. for lower levels. Wash, rinse, repeat...start loading up backpacks in the bank to save travelling time. I started this at lvl 3 and it exclusively took me to lvl 10 and brought in enough cash to get decked out in banded, sbshield, combine scimitar, etc. and finance two trade skills to master level. If you like skipping over the completely weak and feeble level, try it out! 
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
